Exponential: Multiplicative

For \[y = \alpha e^{(\beta x + \epsilon)}\] with \(\epsilon \sim N(0,\sigma)\)

\[\begin{align*} xRange &= (0, 20)\\ N &= 20\\ \alpha & = \frac{1}{e^{\frac{\sigma^2}{2}}}\\ \epsilon &\sim N(0, \sigma) \end{align*}\]

See alpha-calculation.pdf for \(\alpha\) calculations.
